<h1>Jeff Bajorek</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://parabolasales.com/now/">parabolasales.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Novi
MI
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Sales Leader, Sales Coach
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I turn good salespeople into great salespeople.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Someone took me under their wing and showed me what it meant to be a great salesperson.  I learned well, and I want to do that for others.  Most sales managers are not allowed to do that for one reason or another.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Never underestimate the power of doing something before you know how difficult it could be. -or- I know we’re told that we’re all unique snowflakes, but if something matters to you, you’re not the only one, and there have never been more ways to connect with the others.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“The Icarus Deception” by Seth Godin, ”The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People” by Stephen Covey
</p>

